description:
This is a 14 minute workout called '12 Minute Hip Mobility Routine (FOLLOW ALONG)' from the channel Tom Merrick.
The workout falls under Flexibility/Stretching.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Reboot Workout and The Foundation Builder vibe.
The technique difficulty is Intermediate and Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: NEW SQUAT FLEXIBILITY PROGRAM IN APP: https://www.bodyweightwarrior.co.uk/app
PDF DOWNLOAD: https://www.bodyweightwarrior.co.uk/blog/12-min-hip-mobility-routine

INSTAGRAM: @TheBodyweightWarriors
https://www.instagram.com/thebodyweightwarrior/
COACHING: http://www.bodyweightwarrior.co.uk/online-coaching/

FOLLOW ALONG ROUTINES: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLXi7slewxuMJ5X0qMqgipbWjBGWqJnUV8

This video shares a 12-minute hip flexibility routine for improving internal and external rotation of the hip as well as squat flexibility. This routine is a good warm-up or cool down for a squat session.
